FKWMHC5-1 01/20/2026 GED (L)GED 2025-3192 SUB SB94
JUDICIARY SUBSTITUTE TO SB94
OFFERED BY SENATOR BARFOOT
1
2
3
4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, an individual who parks in a
6 designated disability access parking place without
7 proper authorization will face varying penalties.
8 This bill would provide that an individual who
9 is not an individual with a disability or who is not
10 transporting an individual with a disability and uses a
11 distinctive disability license plate or placard to park
12 in a designated disability access parking place shall
13 be guilty of a Class B misdemeanor.
14
15
16 A BILL
17 TO BE ENTITLED
18 AN ACT
19
20 Relating to disabled parking; to amend Sections
21 32-6-233 and 40-12-300, Code of Alabama 1975, to further
22 provide for the unauthorized used of designated parking
23 places.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. Sections 32-6-233 and 40-12-300, Code of
26 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
27 "§32-6-233
28 (a) Any person who meets any of the following shall be
