(a) Any person who meets any of the following shall be
29 guilty of a Class B misdemeanor:
30 (1)a. The person is not an individual with a long-term
31 or temporary disability, or who is not an owner of a vehicle
32 primarily transporting an individual with a disability;, and
33 who
34 b. The person willfully and falsely represents himself
35 or herself as an individual with a long-term or temporary
36 disability or as an owner of a vehicle primarily transporting
37 an individual with a disability to obtain the distinctive
38 special access or disability access license plates, or
39 removable windshield placards, or both, prescribed by this
