51 be guilty of a Class B misdemeanor and, upon conviction, shall
52 be punished according to law.
53 (5) The person is not an individual with a long-term or
54 temporary disability and uses a distinctive special access or
55 disability access license plate, or removable windshield
56 placard, or both, to park a motor vehicle in a parking place
Page 2

placard, or both, to park a motor vehicle in a parking place
57 designated for individuals with disabilities.
58 (6) The person is not an owner of a vehicle primarily
59 transporting an individual with a disability and uses a
60 distinctive special access or disability access license plate,
61 or removable windshield placard, or both, to park a motor
62 vehicle in a parking place designated for individuals with
63 disabilities.
64 (b) Any person who misuses or abuses the parking
65 privileges protected by this division by parking in designated
66 special access parking or disability access spaces with
67 expired removable windshield placards shall be guilty of a
68 Class C misdemeanor and, upon conviction, shall be punished
