70 (c)(1) This section may be enforced by any law
71 enforcement officer who has successfully complied with the
72 minimum standards for police officers as set forth in Section
73 36-21-46, including municipal law enforcement officers,
74 sheriffs, deputy sheriffs, and Alabama State Troopers.
75 (2) Any law enforcement officer enforcing this section
76 may ask for verification that either the driver or a passenger
77 of the parked vehicle is the lawful holder of a distinctive
78 special access or disability access license plate or placard."
79 "§40-12-300
80 (a)(1) The distinctive license plates provided for
81 herein shall be prepared by the Commissioner of Revenue and
82 shall be issued through the county license issuing officials
83 of the state in the same manner as are other motor vehicle
84 license plates. An applicant for a distinctive plate shall
Page 3

license plates. An applicant for a distinctive plate shall
85 present to the issuing official documentation that he or she
86 is either of the following:
87 a. A parent, stepparent, or legal guardian of a minor
88 or an adult who is an individual with a disability as defined
89 in Section 32-6-230.
90 b. An individual with a disability as defined in
91 Section 32-6-230.
92 (2) Upon presentation of the required documentation,
93 the applicant shall be issued the requested number of special
94 access or disability access distinctive license plates upon
95 the payment of the regular license fee, as provided by law.
96 (b) Any private agency, nursing home, church, or
97 charitable institution that submits to the licensing authority
98 proof satisfactory to the commissioner that it operates a
99 motor vehicle for the primary purpose of transporting one or
100 more individuals with disabilities may apply for the
101 distinctive plates. Applicants shall pay the regular fees for
102 license plates, as provided by law.
103 (c) Any government agency that applies for a license
104 plate for a vehicle that it owns for the primary purpose of
105 transporting individuals with disabilities shall be issued the
106 requested number of license plates according to Section
107 40-12-250, with the plate displaying the Dynamic Accessibility
108 Symbol embossed on the plate.
109 (d) The distinctive license plates shall be used only
110 upon and for personally-owned, private, or government owned
111 and operated passenger vehicles, including, but not limited
112 to, vans, station wagons, buses, motorcycles, and pickup
Page 4

to, vans, station wagons, buses, motorcycles, and pickup
113 trucks, registered in the name of the individual or public or
114 private agency, nursing home, church, or charitable
115 institution making application therefor, and when issued to
116 the applicant shall be used upon the vehicle for which issued
117 in lieu of the standard license plates normally issued for the
118 vehicle. This division shall not be construed to require an
119 individual with a disability to display a distinctive special
120 access or disability access license plate. It is specifically
121 provided that this division shall be construed in pari materia
122 with Section 32-6-231. The commissioner may adopt any rules
123 necessary to carry out this division.
124 (e) The commissioner may require all individuals with
125 long-term disabilities to be recertified by a licensed
126 physician before special access parking or disability access
127 parking license plates may be reissued.
128 (f) Notwithstanding any provision of this section, a
129 motor vehicle may not be parked in an area reserved for
130 individuals with disabilities to park, in a manner as
131 prescribed in Section 32-6-233, shall be subject to the
132 penalties provided therein.unless the individual with a
133 disability is in the vehicle."
134 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
135 1, 2026.
